## ðŸ§ª Lab 1: Setup & EF Core Basics

* Created .NET console app
* Installed EF Core packages for SQL Server

```bash
dotnet new console -n RetailInventory
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.SqlServer
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Design
```

---

## ðŸ§ª Lab 2: Define Models & DbContext

* Created `Product` and `Category` models
* Added `AppDbContext` with connection string

---

## ðŸ§ª Lab 3: Create & Apply Migrations

* Installed EF CLI
* Added migration and created database

```bash
dotnet ef migrations add InitialCreate
dotnet ef database update
```

---

## ðŸ§ª Lab 4: Insert Initial Data

* Inserted sample categories and products
* Used `AddRangeAsync()` and `SaveChangesAsync()`

---

## ðŸ§ª Lab 5: Read Data

* Retrieved data using `ToListAsync()`, `FindAsync()`, and `FirstOrDefaultAsync()`
* Displayed product info in console

---

## ðŸ§ª Lab 6: Update & Delete

* Updated product price
* Deleted product by name

